1 AN ACT relating to economic development, making an appropriation therefor, and
2 declaring an emergency.
3 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
4 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF SUBCHAPTER 20 OF KRS CHAPTER
5 154 IS CREATED TO READ AS FOLLOWS:
6 (1) As used in this section:
7 (a) "Eligible recipient" means:
8 1. A nonprofit corporation organized under 26 U.S.C. sec. 501(c);
9 2. A city or county government; or
10 3. An industrial development authority located in a rural county;
11 (b) "Eligible use" means financing support to an eligible recipient:
12 1. To assist with compliance risk mitigation for new markets tax credits;
13 or
14 2. Issue low-interest loans to eligible recipients to assist with
15 construction of new buildings or renovation of existing buildings for
16 lease to target wage economic development projects where a recipient
17 will serve as a lessor;
18 (c) "Fund" means the rural building and job creation revolving fund
19 established in this section;
20 (d) "Rural county" means a county having a county population ranking score
21 greater than or equal to ninety-seven (97), as determined by the cabinet
22 under KRS 154.21-017; and
23 (e) "Target wage" means wages paid to residents of a rural county that are
24 greater than or equal to three hundred percent (300%) of the federal
25 minimum wage.
26 (2) (a) There is hereby established the rural building and job creation revolving
27 fund. The authority shall deploy the funds to an eligible recipient for an
Page 1 of 4
