UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 469
1 eligible use.
2 (b) The cabinet shall administer the fund.
3 (c) The fund shall consist of loan repayments, proceeds from financial
4 instruments, appropriations, contributions, donations, gifts, or federal
5 funds.
6 (d) Notwithstanding KRS 45.229, any moneys remaining in the fund at the
7 close of the fiscal year shall not lapse but shall be carried forward into the
8 succeeding fiscal year.
9 (3) The cabinet shall determine the terms and conditions of the agreements deploying
10 moneys from the fund, monitor performance of the economic development
11 projects, and secure reasonable collateral.
12 (4) By November 1, 2026, and May 1, 2027, and each November 1 and May 1
13 thereafter, the cabinet shall prepare a report of the rural building and job
14 creation revolving fund to be submitted to the Governor and the Legislative
15 Research Commission for referral to Interim Joint Committee on Appropriations
16 and Revenue, and shall also make the report available on the cabinet's website.
17 The annual report shall include but not be limited to the following:
18 (a) A summary of the eligible loan applications received and relevant statistics
19 relating to actions taken by the cabinet and loans awarded, including the
20 applicant, loan amount, administrative costs, associated fees, and the
21 purpose of the funding;
22 (b) The current balance of the fund;
23 (c) Recommendations regarding appropriations to the fund for the upcoming
24 fiscal year; and
25 (d) Recommendations for legislation or policy actions needed to facilitate
26 greater receipt of grant funding to eligible loan applicants.
27 SECTION 2. A NEW SECTION OF SUBCHAPTER 12 OF KRS CHAPTER
Page 2 of 4
