UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 469
1 154 IS CREATED TO READ AS FOLLOWS:
2 (1) The cabinet shall work closely with the workforce liaison appointed by the
3 president of the Kentucky Community and Technical College System to:
4 (a) Promote jobs created in the Commonwealth as a result of economic
5 development incentive programs; and
6 (b) Provide support with the goal of recruitment and placement of system
7 students and graduates into new job and workforce training opportunities
8 as they are made available within the Commonwealth.
9 (2) The cabinet shall work closely with the system and involve it in policy discussions
10 and planning that may have an effect on community members, system staff, and
11 students.
12 Section 3. The Cabinet for Economic Development’s various incentive
13 programs play a vital role in supporting economic development and job growth
14 throughout the Commonwealth. To ensure companies operating within the
15 Commonwealth’s border counties are not negatively impacted by employees residing in
16 adjacent states and to encourage companies operating in adjacent states to hire Kentucky
17 residents, the cabinet is encouraged to conduct a feasibility and impact study on interstate
18 reciprocity between state economic development programming. The study shall at a
19 minimum identify any existing models, identify the potential economic impacts of such
20 an arrangement between Kentucky and adjacent states, assess the feasibility and cost
21 implications of implementing those models, and provide recommendations. The cabinet
22 shall collaborate with the Center for Economic and Entrepreneurial Development at
23 Murray State University to establish the scope of the study. If the cabinet completes such
24 a study, it shall be submitted to the Interim Joint Committee on Economic Development
25 and Workforce Investment by December 1, 2028.
26 Section 4. Notwithstanding KRS 45.229, the balance of the General Fund
27 appropriation authorized in 2022 Ky. Acts ch. 199, Part I, B., 1., (12) shall not lapse and
